average_pixel box_id viewer_id region.description: Calculates the average pixel value for the region.

create_box box_id.description: Creates a new box for displaying information.

hide_boundary viewer_id.description: Hide the boudary of amplifiers in the specified viewer.

hot_pixel viewer_id threshold region.description: Calculates the hot pixels within the threshold for the region.

read_mouse viewer_id box_id.description: Tracks the mouse inside of the view "viewer_id" and displays the information in the box "box_id".

show_boundary viewer_id.description: Show the boudary of amplifiers in the specified viewer.

show_viewer viewer_id.description: Maximizes a viewer and brings it to the front of the window.

uv_freq viewer_id time_in_millis.description: Changes the frequency for checking for new images from the Rest Server.

uv_load_new viewer_id.description: If in a paused LSST.state and there is a new image available, calling this command will load the new image without changing the LSST.state.

uv_pause viewer_id.description: Pauses the automatic retrieval of new images from the Rest Server.

uv_resume viewer_id.description: Pauses the automatic retrieval of new images from the Rest Server.

uv_start viewer_id.description: Begins the update viewer cycle for a viewer.

uv_update viewer_id.description: Updates a viewer immediately, bypassing the update_viewer_freq interval.
